Vice President Kamala Harris gave a speech in Washington, D.C., expressing the importance of the upcoming election and the need to protect democracy. She emphasized the foundational principles of freedom, justice, and equality, and criticized the recent attacks on voting rights and LGBTQ rights. Harris highlighted the global impact of the election, stating that dictators and autocrats are watching and using the actions of the United States as an example. She praised the accomplishments of the Democratic Party in areas such as healthcare, prescription medication costs, lead pipe removal, broadband access, and climate change. Harris urged the audience to continue their efforts to inform and motivate voters, emphasizing that when people are active and vote, positive changes occur. She concluded by stating that fighting for what is right leads to victory.